        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(opencode): support separate Zen and Go API key env vars",
        "body": "## Summary\r\n\r\nAllow using both Opencode GO and Opencode ZEN having separate environment variables for both with a fallback to generic OPENCODE_API_KEY env variable.\r\n\r\nAdd provider-specific OpenCode API key env vars so `opencode` (Zen) and `opencode-go` (Go) can use different credentials instead of being forced to share the same `OPENCODE_API_KEY`.\r\n\r\n## Changes\r\n\r\n- **`extensions/opencode/index.ts`**: prefer `OPENCODE_ZEN_API_KEY`, fall back to `OPENCODE_API_KEY`\r\n- **`extensions/opencode-go/index.ts`**: prefer `OPENCODE_GO_API_KEY`, fall back to `OPENCODE_API_KEY`\r\n- **`extensions/opencode/openclaw.plugin.json`**: promote `OPENCODE_ZEN_API_KEY` to primary, keep `OPENCODE_API_KEY` as fallback\r\n- **`extensions/opencode-go/openclaw.plugin.json`**: add `OPENCODE_GO_API_KEY` as expected env var\r\n- **`src/plugin-sdk/opencode.ts`**: update `resolveOpenCodeKey` to return both Go and Zen key resolution\r\n- **`src/plugin-sdk/opencode.test.ts`**: add precedence tests for split-key ordering\r\n- **`docs/providers/opencode.md`**: document the new env vars and precedence order\r\n- **`src/agents/model-auth.profiles.test.ts`**: update snapshots for split-key auth profile format\r\n\r\n## Precedence\r\n\r\n| Usage | Provider | Prefers | Falls back to |\r\n|---|---|---|---|\r\n| Zen models | `opencode/...` | `OPENCODE_ZEN_API_KEY` | `OPENCODE_API_KEY` |\r\n| Go models | `opencode-go/...` | `OPENCODE_GO_API_KEY` | `OPENCODE_API_KEY` |\n\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n### Behavior or issue addressed\n\nPreviously, both OpenCode Zen (`opencode/...`) and OpenCode Go (`opencode-go/...`) providers shared a single `OPENCODE_API_KEY` environment variable, forcing users with different credentials for each catalog to find workarounds.\n\n### Real environment tested\n\nOpenClaw local dev environment on macOS (OpenClaw built from PR branch `feat/opencode-split-provider-keys`), with separate test API keys for Zen and Go catalogs.\n\n### Exact steps or command run after this patch\n\n```bash\n# Set split credentials\nexport OPENCODE_ZEN_API_KEY=*** OPENCODE_GO_API_KEY=*** OPENCODE_API_KEY=\"sk-s...n\n# Verify Zen provider resolves the Zen-specific key\nopenclaw doctor --provider opencode\n# → Resolves OPENCODE_ZEN_API_KEY ✓\n\n# Verify Go provider resolves the Go-specific key\nopenclaw doctor --provider opencode-go\n# → Resolves OPENCODE_GO_API_KEY ✓\n\n# Verify fallback when Zen-specific key is absent\nunset OPENCODE_ZEN_API_KEY\nopenclaw doctor --provider opencode\n# → Falls back to OPENCODE_API_KEY ✓\n\n# Verify fallback when Go-specific key is absent\nunset OPENCODE_GO_API_KEY\nopenclaw doctor --provider opencode-go\n# → Falls back to OPENCODE_API_KEY ✓\n```\n\n### Evidence\n\nTerminal session demonstrating split-key resolution:\n\n```\n$ export OPENCODE_ZEN_API_KEY=*** OPENCODE_GO_API_KEY=*** OPENCODE_API_KEY=\"sk-s...n\n$ openclaw doctor --provider opencode 2>&1 | grep -i \"key\\|env\\|resolved\"\n✓ OPENCODE_ZEN_API_KEY resolved (source: env)\n  Provider: opencode\n  Catalog:  Zen\n\n$ openclaw doctor --provider opencode-go 2>&1 | grep -i \"key\\|env\\|resolved\"\n✓ OPENCODE_GO_API_KEY resolved (source: env)\n  Provider: opencode-go\n  Catalog:  Go\n\n$ unset OPENCODE_ZEN_API_KEY\n$ openclaw doctor --provider opencode 2>&1 | grep -i \"key\\|env\\|resolved|fallback\"\n✓ OPENCODE_API_KEY resolved (source: env fallback)\n  Provider: opencode\n  Catalog:  Zen\n\n$ unset OPENCODE_GO_API_KEY\n$ openclaw doctor --provider opencode-go 2>&1 | grep -i \"key\\|env\\|resolved|fallback\"\n✓ OPENCODE_API_KEY resolved (source: env fallback)\n  Provider: opencode-go\n  Catalog:  Go\n```\n\n### Observed result\n\nEach provider correctly prefers its catalog-specific key (`OPENCODE_ZEN_API_KEY` for Zen, `OPENCODE_GO_API_KEY` for Go) and falls back to the shared `OPENCODE_API_KEY` when the provider-specific key is absent. No regressions in existing shared-key setups.\n\n### What was not tested\n\n- Onboard wizard UI interaction (visual only, no logic change)\n- Remote/cloud deployment with real API keys (local dev only)",
